
[1]glasswort

   GL`ASSWORT, n. A plant, the Salsola, of several species, all which may
   be used in the manufacture of glass. The Barilla of commerce, is the
   semifused ashes of the Salsola soda, which is largely cultivated on the
   Mediterranean in Spain.
